      <p id="line-height">I am a 23 year old full-stack <b class="bold">developer</b> with a passion for <b class="bold">front-end design</b>. I'm passionate about making a site look as clean as possible and everything that goes along with that. Back when I was teaching skiing I used to claim that "if it looks good, it is good" and I maintain that mantra for web development.
      <br>
      <br>
      I grew up in Surrey and lived there for the first 18 years of my life before moving to Plymouth to study Politics and International Relations for 3 years. Post graduation I travelled to the Canadian Rockies where I lived for a couple of years working as a ski Instructor at Mt. Norquay in Banff (pictured).
      <br>
      <br>
      I decided to move back to London in 2017 in order to pursue a career in tech. Having started to teach myself <b class="bold">Ruby</b> and <b class="bold">Javascript</b> with some online courses I took the decision to accelerate my learning and joined Le Wagon's intensive nine-week coding bootcamp. During the course of this programme my team designed <%= link_to "voyagr.co.uk", "https://www.voyagr.co.uk/", target: "_blank", class: "voyagr" %>, a facebook chatbot which provides personalised travel suggestions, this gave me valuable experience designing mobile first web pages.
      <br>
      <br>
      Following the bootcamp I was asked to return as a teaching assistant for the next batch of students, this has allowed me to consolidate my knowledge as well as providing me with the opportunity of <b class="bold">debugging</b> code written in a variety of different styles. I currently do freelance work alongside my teaching responsibilities, if you are interested in having me build a website for you, please click on one the media links below, cheers.
